<!-- SECTION 2: TOP PIPELINE -->
<section class="hidden" id="top">
<h2>TOP Pipeline</h2>
<p>Texture OPerators are the visual backbone of TouchDesigner. Each TOP processes image data on the GPU, passing textures through a chain of compositing, filtering, warping, and feedback operations. The result feeds directly to output or into other operator families.</p>
<div class="canvas-wrap">
<canvas height="220" id="topCanvas"></canvas>
<div class="canvas-label">live TOP pipeline — drag to connect</div>
</div>
<div class="slider-row">
<label>Feedback Gain</label>
<input id="fbGainSlider" max="100" min="0" type="range" value="80"/>
<span id="fbGainVal">80%</span>
</div>
<div class="slider-row">
<label>Blur Amount</label>
<input id="blurSlider" max="100" min="0" type="range" value="30"/>
<span id="blurVal">30</span>
</div>
<div style="margin-top:1rem">
<span class="node-badge node-top">Noise TOP</span> →
    <span class="node-badge node-top">Feedback TOP</span> →
    <span class="node-badge node-top">Blur TOP</span> →
    <span class="node-badge node-top">Level TOP</span> →
    <span class="node-badge node-top">Out TOP</span>
</div>
<div class="card-grid">
<div class="card"><h3>Feedback TOP</h3><p>Routes the output texture back to an input, creating persistent visual memory. The gain parameter controls decay rate. Essential for trails, plasma, and recursive patterns.</p></div>
<div class="card"><h3>Noise TOP</h3><p>Generates procedural noise textures: Alligator, Sparse, Hermite, Random. Animated over time to produce organic movement without source material.</p></div>
<div class="card"><h3>Composite TOP</h3><p>Blends two textures using 20+ blend modes: Add, Multiply, Screen, Overlay, Difference. The building block of layered visual systems.</p></div>
<div class="card"><h3>GLSL TOP</h3><p>Runs custom fragment shaders directly on GPU. The most powerful operator for bespoke visual effects. Exposes full GLSL ES 3.0 capability.</p></div>
</div>
</section>
<div class="divider"></div>
<!-- SECTION 3: GLSL SHADERS -->
<section class="hidden" id="glsl">
<h2>GLSL Shaders in TouchDesigner</h2>
<p>GLSL TOP and GLSL MAT operators give direct GPU access. TouchDesigner wraps standard GLSL with a set of uniforms (time, resolution, channel inputs) that make shader development fast. Live coding with immediate visual feedback is the standard workflow.</p>
<div class="canvas-wrap">
<canvas height="240" id="glslCanvas"></canvas>
<div class="canvas-label">shader preview — mouse for UV distortion</div>
</div>
<div class="slider-row">
<label>UV Distort Amount</label>
<input id="uvDistSlider" max="100" min="0" type="range" value="40"/>
<span id="uvDistVal">40</span>
</div>
<div class="slider-row">
<label>Color Cycle Speed</label>
<input id="cycleSlider" max="100" min="0" type="range" value="50"/>
<span id="cycleVal">50</span>
</div>
<div class="info-box">
<strong>TouchDesigner GLSL uniforms:</strong> <code>vec2 vUV</code> (texture coordinate), <code>float sampleRate</code>, <code>int sampleIndex</code>. Channel textures accessed as <code>uniform sampler2D sTD2DInputs[n]</code>. Time available via <code>uniform float uTime</code> (set via Script CHOP or Info CHOP).
  </div>
<div class="card-grid">
<div class="card"><h3>Fragment Shaders</h3><p>GLSL TOP runs a fragment shader over every pixel. vUV gives normalized coordinates. Full floating-point precision for HDR effects.</p></div>
<div class="card"><h3>Geometry Shaders</h3><p>GLSL MAT supports vertex, geometry, and fragment stages. Animate geometry, generate particles, and apply per-vertex lighting in one operator chain.</p></div>
<div class="card"><h3>Compute Shaders</h3><p>TD 2022+ supports compute shaders via GLSL TOP in compute mode. Enables particle systems, fluid simulation, and mass geometry deformation on GPU.</p></div>
<div class="card"><h3>Live Reloading</h3><p>TouchDesigner hot-reloads GLSL files. External editors (VS Code + TD GLSL plugin) enable syntax highlighting and live preview with sub-second iteration.</p></div>
</div>
</section>
<div class="divider"></div>
<!-- SECTION 4: CHOP AUDIO REACTIVE -->
<section class="hidden" id="chop">
<h2>CHOP Audio Reactivity</h2>
<p>Channel OPerators process time-series data: audio, MIDI, OSC, sensor feeds. The audio analysis chain — AudioDevice In → AudioSpectrum → Analyze → Math → Export — turns live sound into control signals that drive any parameter in the network.</p>
<div class="canvas-wrap">
<canvas height="240" id="chopCanvas"></canvas>
<div class="canvas-label">simulated audio spectrum → visual response</div>
</div>
<div class="slider-row">
<label>Bass Drive</label>
<input id="bassSlider" max="100" min="0" type="range" value="60"/>
<span id="bassVal">60</span>
</div>
<div class="slider-row">
<label>Mid Drive</label>
<input id="midSlider" max="100" min="0" type="range" value="50"/>
<span id="midVal">50</span>
</div>
<div class="slider-row">
<label>High Drive</label>
<input id="highSlider" max="100" min="0" type="range" value="40"/>
<span id="highVal">40</span>
</div>
<div style="margin-top:1rem">
<span class="node-badge node-chop">Audio Device In</span> →
    <span class="node-badge node-chop">Audio Spectrum</span> →
    <span class="node-badge node-chop">Analyze</span> →
    <span class="node-badge node-chop">Math</span> →
    <span class="node-badge node-chop">Export → Params</span>
</div>
<div class="card-grid">
<div class="card"><h3>AudioSpectrum CHOP</h3><p>FFT analysis producing frequency spectrum. Configurable bin count (64-4096), windowing function (Hann, Hamming, Blackman). Output: magnitude per frequency bin.</p></div>
<div class="card"><h3>Analyze CHOP</h3><p>Extracts scalar values from multi-channel signals: RMS, peak, average, or frequency-band energy. Converts waveform to control signal.</p></div>
<div class="card"><h3>MIDI In CHOP</h3><p>Receives MIDI CC, note, and clock data. Map note velocity to any parameter. Clock sync enables beat-accurate visual events.</p></div>
<div class="card"><h3>OSC In DAT/CHOP</h3><p>Receives Open Sound Control messages over UDP/TCP. Enables control from phones (TouchOSC), other computers, and modular synths.</p></div>
</div>
</section>
