<!-- SECTION 6: DAT SCRIPTING -->
<section class="hidden" id="dat">
<h2>DAT Scripting &amp; Data</h2>
<p>Data OPerators handle text, tables, and Python scripts. Script DATs run arbitrary Python code with access to the full TD operator tree. Execute callbacks on frame cook, parameter change, MIDI event, or OSC message. The entire TD network is a live Python object graph.</p>
<div class="canvas-wrap">
<canvas height="220" id="datCanvas"></canvas>
<div class="canvas-label">data flow visualization</div>
</div>
<div class="info-box">
<strong>Core Python pattern:</strong> <code>op('noise1').par.transform.val = 1.5</code>. Access any parameter on any operator by name. <code>me.cook()</code> forces recompute. <code>parent().op('out1')</code> traverses the network hierarchy. Python 3.x full standard library available.
  </div>
<div class="card-grid">
<div class="card"><h3>Script DAT</h3><p>Python code executed on each frame cook or triggered by events. Can read/write parameters, instantiate operators, query CHOP data, and interface with external APIs.</p></div>
<div class="card"><h3>Table DAT</h3><p>Spreadsheet-like data table. Drive operator parameters from CSV, configure routing, store state. Fundamental for data-driven and generative systems.</p></div>
<div class="card"><h3>Web Client DAT</h3><p>HTTP requests from within TD. Pull data from APIs (weather, stock prices, social feeds) and map it directly to visual parameters in real time.</p></div>
<div class="card"><h3>Execute DAT</h3><p>Callbacks for frame start, frame end, parameter change, keyboard, MIDI. The event system for reactive Python scripting throughout the network.</p></div>
</div>
</section>
<div class="divider"></div>
<!-- SECTION 7: NETWORK ARCHITECTURE -->
<section class="hidden" id="network">
<h2>Network Architecture</h2>
<p>Large TD projects decompose into modular Components (COMPs). Base COMPs encapsulate reusable systems; Container COMPs manage complex UI. Replicator COMPs instantiate operator sets dynamically. The network is a live scene graph that can be edited and extended during performance.</p>
<div class="canvas-wrap">
<canvas height="240" id="networkCanvas"></canvas>
<div class="canvas-label">operator network — click nodes</div>
</div>
<div class="card-grid">
<div class="card"><h3>Component (COMP)</h3><p>Container for sub-networks. Base COMP is a blank container; Geometry COMP is a 3D scene node; Camera, Light, and Render COMPs define the rendering pipeline.</p></div>
<div class="card"><h3>Replicator COMP</h3><p>Instantiates copies of a master COMP based on a Table DAT. Each row → one instance with unique parameters. Drives generative systems at scale.</p></div>
<div class="card"><h3>Perform Mode</h3><p>Hides the editor and runs TD in full-screen output mode. Custom UI panels built inside TD control the performance. Parameter panels stay accessible via keyboard shortcuts.</p></div>
<div class="card"><h3>Multi-Output</h3><p>TD supports multi-window, multi-monitor, and Spout/Syphon output simultaneously. A single network can drive multiple projectors via separate Out TOPs.</p></div>
</div>
</section>
