<!-- SECTION 9: GLOSSARY -->
<section class="hidden" id="glossary">
<h2>Glossary</h2>
<p>Core vocabulary of TouchDesigner and node-based real-time visual synthesis.</p>
<dl class="glossary-grid">
<div class="glossary-item"><dt>TOP</dt><dd>Texture OPerator. Processes 2D image data on the GPU. All TOP outputs are textures. Named for their blue color in the TD network editor.</dd></div>
<div class="glossary-item"><dt>CHOP</dt><dd>Channel OPerator. Processes time-series data (audio, MIDI, sensor, animation curves). Output: channels of floating-point samples.</dd></div>
<div class="glossary-item"><dt>SOP</dt><dd>Surface OPerator. Handles 3D geometry: polygons, NURBS, particles, and point clouds. Green in the network editor.</dd></div>
<div class="glossary-item"><dt>MAT</dt><dd>Material OPerator. Defines surface shading: PBR, phong, wireframe, GLSL custom. Applied to geometry in Geometry COMPs.</dd></div>
<div class="glossary-item"><dt>DAT</dt><dd>Data OPerator. Handles text, tables, and Python scripts. The scripting backbone and data management layer of TD. Purple in the editor.</dd></div>
<div class="glossary-item"><dt>COMP</dt><dd>Component OPerator. Container for sub-networks (Base COMP), 3D scenes (Geometry COMP), and UI elements (Container COMP).</dd></div>
<div class="glossary-item"><dt>Feedback TOP</dt><dd>Routes its own output back as input with a one-frame delay. Enables persistent visual memory, decay trails, and recursive pattern generation.</dd></div>
<div class="glossary-item"><dt>GLSL TOP</dt><dd>Runs a custom fragment shader over a texture. The most flexible visual operator in TD. Access to all inputs as sampler2D uniforms.</dd></div>
<div class="glossary-item"><dt>Replicator COMP</dt><dd>Instantiates a master component N times, where N is driven by a Table DAT. Each instance gets unique parameters from table rows.</dd></div>
<div class="glossary-item"><dt>Cook</dt><dd>TD term for "compute." An operator cooks when its inputs change or it is forced to recalculate. Cook time visible in performance metrics panel.</dd></div>
<div class="glossary-item"><dt>Export</dt><dd>Binding a CHOP channel to an operator parameter. Right-click any parameter → Export → select CHOP channel. Updates on every cook.</dd></div>
<div class="glossary-item"><dt>Expression</dt><dd>Python expression evaluated live as a parameter value. E.g., <code>op('noise1').par.tx</code> in a parameter field. Updates every frame.</dd></div>
<div class="glossary-item"><dt>Spout / Syphon</dt><dd>Cross-application GPU texture sharing. Spout (Windows), Syphon (macOS). Share textures between TD and Resolume, MadMapper, VDMX, OBS.</dd></div>
<div class="glossary-item"><dt>NDI</dt><dd>Network Device Interface. Low-latency video streaming over LAN. TD supports NDI In/Out for sending video between machines on the same network.</dd></div>
<div class="glossary-item"><dt>Perform Mode</dt><dd>Full-screen output mode hiding the TD editor. Custom UI panels (Container COMPs) provide performance control without editor overhead.</dd></div>
<div class="glossary-item"><dt>KinectAzure CHOP</dt><dd>Driver for the Azure Kinect depth/skeleton sensor. Provides 3D skeleton joint positions as CHOP channels for body-tracking reactive visuals.</dd></div>
<div class="glossary-item"><dt>TD Commercial License</dt><dd>Commercial license required for for-profit use: $300/year (indie) or $600/year (pro). Educational/non-commercial use is free.</dd></div>
<div class="glossary-item"><dt>Instancing</dt><dd>Rendering millions of geometry copies with per-instance attributes (position, color, scale). Driven by CHOP or SOP data via Instancing toggle on Geometry COMP.</dd></div>
<div class="glossary-item"><dt>USD / FBX Import</dt><dd>TD 2022+ supports USD scene import. FBX and Alembic for animated geometry. Enables integration with Blender, Houdini, and Maya pipelines.</dd></div>
<div class="glossary-item"><dt>OSC</dt><dd>Open Sound Control. Flexible message protocol over UDP. Map OSC messages to TD parameters for control from phones, tablets, or external software.</dd></div>
<div class="glossary-item"><dt>Derivative Forum</dt><dd>TouchDesigner's primary community resource at derivative.ca/forum. Search before posting — most questions answered in existing threads with file examples.</dd></div>
</dl>
</section>
